      {
        "id": "PSwEG_8gjhk_0l1P",
        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Problem 4.1</strong></p><p><strong>Percent: Out of 100</strong></p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "u6wNGjNjSIheipmG",
        "title": "Text 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<li>Mr. Satyam asks his students if they liked doing fundraisers. Seventy-eight out of his 100 sixth-grade students said yes. </li><ul><li>What percent of the sixth-grade students like fundraisers? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "U6ogBdTxsIkqu8TZ",
        "title": "Text 3",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>78%</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "iCJdB8xOS9_7Ib8V",
        "title": "Text 4",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Mr. Satyam suggests that a grid or a bar would be visual way to represent percent,</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "sG-lTYEkEInCSlm8",
        "title": "Grid",
        "content": {
          "type": "Image",
          "url": "cq/images/grid.png",
          "filename": "cq/images/grid.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "hQP2L0B8JQM6TxG4",
        "title": "Bar",
        "content": {
          "type": "Image",
          "url": "cq/images/bar.png",
          "filename": "cq/images/bar.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "xJptKr0PrmXhgMd8",
        "title": "Text 5",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>How can the sixth-grade data be represented on the grid? On the bar? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "q8QnNANUiiXohptU",
        "title": "Text 6",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>On the grid, we can shade 78 full squares out of the 100 total.</p><p>On the bar, we can shade 7 full sections and 8 pieces of a full section.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "flg1Ah4Tn-naYKn9",
        "title": "Grid Answer",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Image",
          "url": "cq/images/grid-answer.png",
          "filename": "cq/images/grid-answer.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "C54gA0011KK9hxfX",
        "title": "Bar answer",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Image",
          "url": "cq/images/bar-answer.png",
          "filename": "cq/images/bar-answer.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "Ru5Kb6LYrblSqwkF",
        "title": "Text 7",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Mr. Satyam also teaches 50 seventh graders. Thirty-eight of them liked doing the fundraiser. How would this data be represented on a grid? On a bar? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "UnNab_ukp7HupgZh",
        "title": "Text 8",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>On the grid or the bar, we can shade 38 sections out of the 50 total and another 38 sections out of the 50 total. This is a total of 76 out of 100, or 76%.</p><p>Note that combining ratios is different than adding fractions. With fractions, we add the number of pieces (numerators) and keep the size of the pieces (the denominator) the same. With ratios, we combine both quantities. We are not adding the ratios; we are scaling up the quantities to find equivalent ratios.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "6qkyJmXdSkbXEkWp",
        "title": "Seventh graders fundraiser",
        "content": {
          "type": "Image",
          "url": "cq/images/7th-grade-answer.png",
          "filename": "cq/images/7th-grade-answer.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "p8nt0OiVUDddo7C5",
        "title": "Text 9",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Between the seventh graders or sixth graders, which group has the larger percent who like doing the fundraiser? Explain your reasoning.</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "PJXPCGXcLteAzMVz",
        "title": "Text 10",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>The sixth graders have a larger percent of students who like doing the fundraiser. 78% &gt; 76% </p>"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  },
